The Health Department has recorded 3 159 new COVID-19 cases, pushing the number of total infections to 1 482 412. There have been a further 276 COVID-19 related deaths in the country, bringing the national death toll to 47 145. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in Gauteng. “Regrettably, we report 276 more COVID-19 related deaths: 33 from Eastern Cape, 20 from the Free State, 126 from Gauteng, 34 from KwaZulu-Natal, 3 from Limpopo, 21 from Mpumalanga, 8 from Northern Cape and 31 from the Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. The total number of recoveries stands at 1 374 368. The cumulative total number of tests conducted to date is 8 573 464. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 482 412, the total number of deaths is 47 145 and the total number of recoveries is 1 374 368. pic.twitter.com/MYVoTxtJ5n — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) February 10, 2021 